		<div class="postBody entry-content">
			<p>There is no need to host CPU-intensive thumbnailing scripts like this on your webserver anymore. Instead, you can use a specialized service for remote, on-demand image manipulation like <a href="http://steadyoffload.com/thumbnail-problem" rel="nofollow">SteadyOffload</a>.</p>
<p>All you have to do is use a custom HTML attribute called &#8220;xmanip&#8221; with the img tag. This will deliver the thumbnail from one of the globally scattered cache servers:</p>
<p>&lt;img srcx=&#8221;image.jpg&#8221; xmanip=&#8221;RescaleWidth 130&#8243; /&gt;</p>
<p>So much easier than all the hassle with GD or ImageMagick! Moreover, this reduces the CPU load of your webserver and saves some bandwidth.</p>
					</div>
